      {
        "id": 2238566,
        "name": null,
        "username": "jcoley3",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/jcoley3/{size}/507_2.png",
        "created_at": "2017-08-14T04:12:28.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"William Kelley\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n William Kelley:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Caillot is / was a cousin of Pierre Morey\u2019s. He had the B\u00e2tard <em>en metayage,</em> the other half going to Louis Jadot. When I last saw Jacques Lardi\u00e8re he described Caillot as a grower who knew how to produce a generous crop.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>In light of Mr. Lardiere\u2019s inability to make a Grand Cru (or any White Burgundy) that didn\u2019t oxidize within five years or so for most of my adult lifetime, it\u2019s rich to hear him trash talk anyone about anything wine related.</p>",
